CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1946, pg. 2, reads: "Instructor - After attending the Race Relations Institute at Fisk University, Miss Eileen Schulte, instructor in English at the University of Minnesota, came to Pittsburgh and visited several Hill District institutions, including The Pittsburgh Courier plant and the Urban League headquarters. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: P. L. Prattis and Eileen Schulte seated at desk in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper offices
